FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,FDevlin was appointed as an Associate
OL,7,FSolicitor at Cartmell Shepherd in the
OL,8,FWills, Probate, and Inheritance Team
OL,9,Fin 2019 after being formally
OL,10,Fregistered as a solicitor 11 years ago.
OL,12,FHe did his law degree at the
OL,13,FUniversity of Cumbria in Carlisle.
OL,15,FThe irregularities were discovered
OL,16,Fafter one of the directors at Cartmell
OL,17,FShepherd identified a 'worrying
OL,18,Fpattern' of how he was submitting
OL,19,Finformation to the law firm.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/8
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,FThe firm carried out an internal
OL,7,Finvestigation, during which Devlin
OL,8,Fadmitted his conduct and justified it
OL,9,Fby blaming his workload.
OL,11,FHe said that "his actions had clearly
OL,12,Fnot been right" and that he was under
OL,13,Fpressure to make his targets, adding
OL,14,Fthat it was his "workload that had led
OL,15,Fhim to making the decisions."
OL,17,FHe added that he had not made any
OL,18,Ffinancial gain from his misdemeanours.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/8
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,FDevlin was then referred to the
OL,7,Fregulatory body the Solicitors
OL,8,FRegulation Authority (SRA).
OL,10,FHe admitted to the tribunal that he
OL,11,Fhad been creating time records that
OL,12,Fwere in excess of the time actually
OL,13,Fspent on client matters between March
OL,14,F2020 and November 2022 and he admitted
OL,15,Fthat his conduct had been dishonest.
OL,17,FBecause he has now been struck off the
OL,18,FRoll of Solicitors, Devlin can no
OL,19,Flonger work as a solicitor.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/8
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,FToday his former employers, Cartmell
OL,7,FShepherd, said: "The individual is no
OL,8,Flonger employed by this company.
OL,10,F"We are aware of the Solicitors
OL,11,FDisciplinary Tribunal's decision. We
OL,12,Ftake professional standards and
OL,13,Fregulatory compliance extremely
OL,14,Fseriously. We referred him to the SRA
OL,15,Ffor his conduct. We also fully
OL,16,Fcooperated at all times with the SRA
OL,17,Fin supporting its investigations and
OL,18,Fthe provision of evidence for the SDT.
OL,19,FWe took immediate action on the client
OL,20,Fmatters at the time too.
OL,26,@oD@QOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/8
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,F"We wish to assure our clients and
OL,7,Fstakeholders that all the excess time
OL,8,Frecorded by him was removed
OL,10,Ffrom the client files, all client
OL,11,Ffunds that were deducted for that
OL,12,Fexcessive time were fully restored and
OL,14,Fwere and have been fully safeguarded.
OL,16,F"All client services have continued
OL,17,Funinterrupted, and we remain committed
OL,18,Fto maintaining the highest standards
OL,19,Fof professional conduct across the
OL,20,Ffirm.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/8
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1777543610
OL,3,CTribunal strikes off solicitor at
OL,4,CCumbrian law firm Cartmell Shepherd
OL,6,F"The regulatory side of things is now
OL,7,Fat an end and an outcome has finally
OL,8,Fbeen reached by the SDT. It
OL,10,Fhas taken the SRA a number of years to
OL,11,Fmove this to a conclusion by the SDT
OL,12,Fwhich has been out of our
OL,14,Fcontrol."
OL,16,FDevlin has also been ordered to pay
OL,17,Ffixed costs of #10,000.
OL,26,@vD@IO]
